<https://linked.data.gov.au/org/sam> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://linked.data.gov.au/org/sam> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://schema.org/Organization> .
<https://linked.data.gov.au/org/sam> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The South Australian Museum has been committed to making Australia’s natural and cultural heritage accessible, engaging and fun for over 165 years. It is a place where families can learn and grow together. Today the Museum is one of the most visited museums in Australia and holds collections of national and international significance. It is a leader in remote and regional community engagement, and in Australian Aboriginal heritage and scientific research."@en .
<https://linked.data.gov.au/org/sam> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://linked.data.gov.au/dataset/bdr/orgs> .
