<https://linked.data.gov.au/org/wa-bio> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The Biodiversity Information Office (BIO) is responsible for making Western Australian biodiversity data more discoverable, accessible, and useable.  To deliver this change, BIO has developed the Dandjoo biodiversity data platform to mobilise data from all environment-related sectors, including government, industry, research, and the community.  BIO’s day-to-day work also includes a program of data-sharing and outreach work, identifying and sourcing priority datasets for release."@en .
